gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Raptors 121, Nets 93
gameRecap.excerpt: The Raptors snap a four-game losing streak as they defeat the Nets, 121-93. Gary Trent Jr. (25 points on 9-12 FG, 5-7 3PT) led Toronto as Immanuel Quickley (24 points, six rebounds) and Scottie Barnes (18 points, 12 rebounds) totaled 42 points. Mikal Bridges led the Nets with 21 points and four rebounds in the loss.
